      <hedline>
        <hl1>SOFTBANK-ARIBA ALLIANCE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Miki Tanikawa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Softbank forms alliance with Ariba to create online business-to-business marketplaces in Japan (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Japan's leading Internet investment company, Softbank, formed an alliance with Ariba, an electronic- commerce company based in Palo Alto, Calif., to create online business-to-business marketplaces in Japan. Under the terms announced by Softbank's president, Masayoshi Son, the company will take a 40 percent stake in Ariba's Japanese subsidiary for 4.3 billion yen, or about $40 million.</p>
        <p>Miki Tanikawa (NYT)</p>
      </block>
